OL,6,GEvery so often the past throws up
OL,7,Glittle mysteries. Sometimes they are
OL,8,Gvery trivial in themselves but can
OL,9,Gstill be a fascinating insight into a
OL,10,Gbygone era.
OL,12,FOne of these mysteries concerns the
OL,13,F5.35pm junction on BBC One on a handful
OL,14,Fof occasions between 1985 and 1988.
OL,16,FAs all Pres fans of a certain age will
OL,17,Fremember, this junction was not voiced
OL,18,Fby the regular announcer. Instead
OL,19,FPhillip Schofield, Andy Crane and the
OL,20,Fother CBBC presenters would do the
OL,21,Flink.
OL,3,CThe junction where the CBBC presenter
OL,4,Cwas the BBC One announcer
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G1/6
