OL,6,FClearly this was an editorial decision
OL,7,F` not just an operational necessity
OL,8,Fbecause they were in the broom
OL,9,Fcupboard.
OL,11,FIt would have been easy enough for the
OL,12,Fregular announcer to record a link or
OL,13,Fuse the lip mic which was apparently
OL,14,Flocated in the main NC1 control room
OL,15,Ffor emergencies. (This happened
OL,16,Fregularly during the link before CBBC
OL,17,Fat 3.50pm after the start of the new
OL,18,Fdaytime schedule in 1986 when the
OL,19,Fregional news stopped providing a
OL,20,Fbuffer.)
OL,3,CThe junction where the CBBC presenter
OL,4,Cwas the BBC One announcer
