OL,6,FBut here's an even bigger question.
OL,8,FThere were a few occasions between 1985
OL,9,Fand 1987 when the regional news moved
OL,10,Fto 5.35pm to accommodate extended
OL,11,Feditions of the Six o'Clock News or
OL,12,Fother special output.
OL,14,FOutside London and the South East, of
OL,15,Fcourse, there would have been a
OL,16,Fstandard opt-out link.
OL,18,FBut what was happening in NC1 Con? Were
OL,19,FPhillip and Andy really linking into
OL,20,FLondon Plus?
OL,3,CThe junction where the CBBC presenter
OL,4,Cwas the BBC One announcer
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G5/6
